# Walkthrough - Local Hosting Setup

I have successfully set up the local environment for KlinikApp. Here is a summary of the steps taken and the current status of the application.

## 1. Infrastructure (Docker)
- **PostgreSQL**: Running on `localhost:5432`
- **Redis**: Running on `localhost:6379`
- Services started in detached mode using `docker-compose up -d`.

## 2. Database (Prisma)
- **Schema**: Synchronized with `npx prisma db push`.
- **Seeding**: Initial data loaded successfully.
  - **Admin**: `admin@demo.com` / `Admin123!`
  - **Doctor**: `doctor@demo.com` / `Doctor123!`
  - **Asistan**: `asistan@demo.com` / `Assist123!`

## 3. Application Services
- **Backend (NestJS)**: Started on `http://localhost:3000`. You can access the API documentation at `http://localhost:3000/api/docs`.
- **Frontend (Next.js)**: Started on `http://localhost:3001`.

## Verification
- [x] Docker containers are healthy.
- [x] Database seeding completed without errors.
- [x] Backend and Frontend servers are running in the background.

> [!NOTE]
> If you need to stop the servers, you can use the terminal to kill the processes or let me know to stop them for you.
